Accelerize Inc. Key Developments

WorldWideMarkets Selects Accelerize's CAKE SaaS Platform to Manage Performance Marketing Program
Jun 26 17
Accelerize and its digital marketing software division, CAKE announced that WorldWideMarkets has selected the CAKE SaaS platform to manage its performance marketing program. With superior tracking and analytics capabilities, CAKE is designed to generate the maximum number of leads efficiently, thus helping to deliver WorldWideMarkets' commitment to provide a customer trading experience in the Forex market.


Accelerize Inc. Announces Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the First Quarter Ended March 31, 2017
May 9 17
Accelerize Inc. announced unaudited consolidated earnings results for the first quarter ended March 31, 2017. For the quarter, the company’s revenues were $5,956,724 compared to $5,864,018 a year ago. Operating income was $225,528 compared to operating loss of $380,151 a year ago. The significant improvement in operating results was attributable to a $479,000 increase in gross profit coupled with a $126,000 reduction in operating expenses. Net loss was $55,224 compared to $583,241 a year ago. EBITDA was $370,201 compared to LBITDA of $104,019 a year ago. Adjusted EBITDA was $589,901 compared to $337,141 a year ago.


Accelerize Inc. Presents at SunTrust Robinson 2017 Internet & Digital Media Conference, May-09-2017 04:00 PM
May 8 17
Accelerize Inc. Presents at SunTrust Robinson 2017 Internet & Digital Media Conference, May-09-2017 04:00 PM. Venue: The Palace Hotel, 2 New Montgomery Street, San Francisco, California, United States. Speakers: Santi Pierini, Chief Operating Officer and President of CAKE Division.


